Q:

.NET Dynamically Get Control By Name

I need to create a .NET control (in ASP.NET) from a string that represents the control's name. Control myList = SomeSystemClass.GetControlByName("DropDownList");

I guess there is some reflection method in the .NET platform that allows this but I have no idea which one. Any ideas? A:

For Server Controls:
Control c = Page.ParseControl("<asp:DropDownList runat='server' />");

Or more specifically for your example:
string ctrlName = "DropDownList";
Control c = Page.ParseControl("<asp:" + ctrlName + " runat='server' />");

For User Controls:
MyControl myControl1 = (MyControl)LoadControl("TempControl_Samples1.ascx");

